Calculate delays from Centrix and timetable data

Source: R/estimate-delays.R
estimate_delays.Rd

Calculate delays from estimated dwell times and timetable data. This function calculates arrival delay, departure delay, excess dwell time, and whether a train was early or late. These are all estimates, as the dwell times on which they are based are also estimates.

Usage

estimate_delays(dwell_times, timetable_subset, id_matching)

Arguments

dwell_times

Data frame containing estimated dwell times. The structure is expected to match the output of estimate_dwell_times(). However, only 6 columns are required for this function to work:

  • signalSignal ID

  • train_idTrain ID (Centrix)

  • stationStation name

  • t_entersDate and time that train enters berth

  • T_move_oneMoving time before coming to a stop at the station

  • T_dwellDwell time at the station

timetable_subset

Processed timetable containing calling patterns. The structure is expected to match the output of wrangle_timetable(). However, only 7 columns are required:

  • train_headerTrain ID (timetable)

  • dt_originDate and time of train origin

  • geoName of location

  • groupGroup name

  • eventEvent name; anything other than 'Arrive' or 'Depart' is ignored

  • wttScheduled time of event

  • tActual time of event

id_matching

Data frame containing a 1-1 mapping from Centrix IDs to timetable IDs. There should be 3 columns:

  • train_idTrain ID (Centrix)

  • train_headerTrain ID (timetable)

  • dt_originDate and time of train origin

Value

A data frame containing 8 columns:

  • signalSignal ID

  • train_idTrain ID (Centrix)

  • stationStation name

  • T_dwellDwell time in seconds

  • arrival_delayArrival delay in seconds, can be negative if the train arrives early

  • departure_delayDeparture delay in seconds, can be negative if the train departs early

  • excess_dwell_timeDifference between actual dwell time and scheduled dwell time. Can be negative if the train spends less time in the station than scheduled

  • earlyLogical vector indicating whether the train arrived at the station earlier than scheduled

See also

estimate_dwell_times() wrangle_timetable() match_ids() delays
